---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout title="Is DO a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 3 Points)" description="DO is a valid Scrabble word worth 3 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It means a musical note or to perform an action. The highest-scoring D+vowel 2-letter combination." keywords="is do a scrabble word, do scrabble, do valid scrabble, do points scrabble, two letter d words, do meaning scrabble, musical note do scrabble">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Is DO a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 3 Points)","description":"DO is a valid Scrabble word worth 3 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It means a musical note or to perform an action.","datePublished":"2026-06-29","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-do-a-scrabble-word"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is DO a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, DO is valid in both TWL (North American) and SOWPODS (International) Scrabble dictionaries. It scores 3 points (D=2, O=1) and has two meanings: the first note of the musical scale, and to perform an action."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What does DO mean in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"DO has multiple meanings: (1) the first note of the musical scale (solfège), (2) to perform or execute an action, (3) a hairdo (informal). It's the highest-scoring D+vowel 2-letter combination at 3 points."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What words can you extend DO into?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"DO extends into many words: DOC (6pts), DOE (4pts), DOG (5pts), DON (4pts), DOR (4pts), DOS (4pts), DOT (4pts), DOW (7pts). DOW is the strongest extension at 7 points thanks to W(4)."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/two-letter-words/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Two-Letter Words</a>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is DO a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 3 Points)</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Yes, DO is a valid Scrabble word worth 3 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It's the first note of the musical scale and one of the most common English verbs. At 3 points, it's the highest-scoring D+vowel 2-letter combination — making it the best quick play when you need to dump D while keeping your rack flexible.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-green-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-950/30 to-emerald-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-green-500/70">✓ VALID</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">DO</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-green-300 font-semibold mb-3">3 points · D=2, O=1 · A musical note / to perform an action</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Valid in both TWL (Tournament Word List) and SOWPODS (Collins Scrabble Words). DO is the first note of the solfège musical scale and one of the most fundamental English verbs. The highest-scoring D+vowel 2-letter word.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Both</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWL + SOWPODS</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4 D-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">In the Bag</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8 O-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Available</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">DO Extensions: Versatile Follow-Ups</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DOW</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DOC</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DOG</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DOE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">4pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DON</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">4pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DOT</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">4pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DOS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">4pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DOR</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">4pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">DO Strategy: Best D+Vowel Play</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Highest D+vowel combo:</span> DO (3pts) ties with DA (3pts) but has more extensions. With D worth 2 points and O being common (8 tiles), DO is your reliable D-dump play. 3 points for 2 tiles is solid value.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Setup for DOW:</span> Play DO near a W-friendly spot. DOW (7pts) scores well and opens further extensions like DOWN (8pts) and DOWRY (12pts). The DO→DOW→DOWN chain creates escalating value.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Parallel cross-scoring:</span> D forms valid 2-letter crosswords with most common tiles. Play DO parallel to existing words for bonus cross-points. D on DLS gives you 4 from that single tile.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Solfège Scale Words</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">DO starts the <span class="text-white font-medium">solfège musical scale</span> — do, re, mi, fa, sol, la, ti. All are valid in Scrabble: DO (3pts), RE (2pts), MI (4pts), FA (5pts), SO (2pts), LA (2pts), TI (2pts). DO scores the second-highest after FA thanks to D's 2-point value.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-da-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is DA a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 3 Points)</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/is-ut-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is UT a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up required</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
